4. Conclusion
The data demonstrated that NiO NPs induced cytotoxicity in a
concentration-dependent manner, which the mechanism may be
through ROS generation and oxidative stress. The crucial results high-
light, for the ﬁrst time, the antioxidant and the protective activities of
essential oil of
P. lentiscus
against cell oxidative damage induced by NiO
NPs. These ﬁndings also showed the guidelines in the placement of NPs
in safety to promote non-hazardous applications of nanotechnology.
